00a0are scheduled to run from 24 to 30 July at\\u00a0Stade de France.\", \"from\": 587, \"to\": 705, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 640, \"end\": 645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999983006091, \"rank\": 1.6993708651388209e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Twenty four teams (12 each for men and women) will compete against each other in their respective tournaments.\", \"from\": 707, \"to\": 817, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the first time, the rugby sevens matches will commence two days before the opening ceremony with the men's preliminary and quarter-final stages.\", \"from\": 819, \"to\": 967, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition will then take a break for the opening ceremony on 26 July before the medal-winning teams are officially unveiled a day later.\", \"from\": 969, \"to\": 1111, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's tournament will be held between 28 and 30 July, culminating with the gold and bronze medal matches.\", \"from\": 1113, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 12 men's teams to have qualified are Argentina, Australia, Fiji, France, Ireland, Japan, Kenya, New Zealand, Samoa, South Africa, USA and Uruguay.\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1267, \"end\": 1276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0926358091646648e-15, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1278, \"end\": 1287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.551886907594808e-17, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"htt